        Far-right leader quits
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/dutch-pm-dick-schoof-resignation-king-willem-alexander.jpg" alt="Dutch PM Dick Schoof confirmed that he will step down, announcing he would submit his resignation to King Willem-Alexander on behalf of the Cabinet" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          Dutch PM Dick Schoof confirmed that he will step down, announcing he would submit his resignation to King Willem-Alexander on behalf of the Cabinet. Credits: EPA Photo</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        The <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-spotlights-h1-1-dutch-government-fell" target="_blank">Dutch government fell</a> when Geert Wilders‚Äô far-right Party for Freedom (PVV) left the ruling coalition over immigration policy. Wilders accused his coalition partners of rejecting his strict 10-point <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-spotlights-h1-2-asylum-proposal" target="_blank">asylum proposal</a>. This plan aimed to halt all asylum applications and suspend family reunification for refugees.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      The leaders of the other coalition parties accused Wilders of prioritizing his interests over the country's needs. Critics argue that the situation means "at least a year and a half of standstill." This also paves the way for more lenient asylum policies. </p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Following an emergency cabinet meeting, PM Dick Schoof resigned, calling Wilders‚Äô move ‚Äúirresponsible and unnecessary.‚Äù Schoof reaffirmed that the rest of the Cabinet, including the conservative VVD, centrist NSC, and farmers‚Äô party BBB, would continue in a "caretaker capacity."</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
         Other opposition parties have already called for elections, with the leaders pointing to a need for "political change."</p>
        </mj-text>
