          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">
         South Korean elections</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
         Summary: Lee Jae-myung clinched the presidential election, which was triggered by the martial law fiasco.</strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Center-left leader Lee Jae-myung defeated conservative Kim Moon-soo to clinch South Korea‚Äôs <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-spotlights-h2-4-presidential-election" target="_blank">presidential election</a>. The impeachment of conservative President Yoon Suk Yeol triggered this election after his failed attempt to impose martial law.  
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       Despite criticisms of being a populist, Lee <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-spotlights-h2-5-restated-support" target="_blank">restated support</a> for South Korea‚Äôs alliance with the US and pushed for practical diplomacy. Significant challenges lie ahead for him, including the US tariff hikes and the world‚Äôs lowest birth ratio. He promised to pursue dialogue and cooperation with North Korea. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Lee‚Äôs presidency begins without a transition period. Lee promises economic reform, social unity, and a practical foreign policy. However, critics pointed out his criminal record, including <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-06-2025-political-scandal" target="_blank">political scandals</a>, and stated that his victory was due as much to his rivals' failings as his strengths.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
