      <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
       Brothers in sanctions
       </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
         Summary: Iran and Russia have a close relationship due to the Western sanctions imposed on them. </strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
            The Iran-Russia drone partnership has become a strong military alliance. This cooperation helps Moscow boost its <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-analysis-h1-6-long-range-strike-capabilities" target="_blank">long-range strike capabilities</a> in Ukraine. Initially, Russia imported Iran‚Äôs Shahed-136 drones as a quick fix. However, it has shifted to full domestic production in the Alabuga Special Economic Zone. This effort relies on Iranian technology and expertise. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        A secret financing structure supports this industrial growth, which is designed to evade Western sanctions. Iran and Russia utilize UAE-based intermediaries, gold payments, and front companies, such as Sahara Thunder, to move assets. Despite US sanctions, this network adapts, showing the limits of Western enforcement against determined state actors.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        The alliance also reflects a larger geopolitical trend. It shows the rise of a parallel defense ecosystem among sanctioned regimes. These regimes are increasingly resistant to traditional Western pressure. By circumventing isolation, Iran and Russia are not just defying sanctions but also undermining them. 
          </p>
         
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
