        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá∏üá™ Sweden - Ending foreign adoptions.</strong> A Swedish inquiry revealed decades of abuse in international adoptions, including child trafficking, falsified documents, and adoptions without parental consent. Countries affected include Sri Lanka, Colombia, and China. The inquiry criticized weak oversight and recommended banning international adoptions, as well as issuing a formal apology (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-worldwide-7-about-international-adoptions" target="_blank">about international adoptions</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá∑üáº Rwanda - M23 crimes.</strong> Rwanda-backed M23 rebels executed at least 21 civilians in Goma, DRC, over two days in February. Victims included a 15-year-old and men shot execution-style near military camps. The violence is part of a broader M23 offensive that has displaced many, amid widespread killings and abductions in eastern Congo (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-worldwide-8-attack-on-civilians" target="_blank">attack on civilians</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáµüá± Poland - Vote of confidence.</strong> Polish PM Donald Tusk has called for a vote of confidence in his government after a stinging presidential election defeat. The victory of right-wing populist Karol Nawrocki threatens to paralyze Tusk‚Äôs legislative agenda via presidential veto (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-worldwide-9-tusk-s-problems" target="_blank">Tusk‚Äôs problems</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá®üá≥ China - Sizing up.</strong> 
           China‚Äôs military activity near Taiwan surged in May, with 70 warships and 75 aircraft deployed in contested areas. Taiwanese officials describe the actions as methodical, involving both gray-zone tactics and high-end assets, such as bombers and aircraft carriers (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-worldwide-10-taiwan-tampering" target="_blank">Taiwan tampering</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá©üá™ Germany- Court rules against it.</strong> 
            A Berlin court has ruled that Germany violated EU asylum law by turning back three Somali nationals at its Polish border. The court found the expulsions unlawful under the Dublin regulation, which obligates Germany to process asylum requests if it is responsible (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-worldwide-11-more-about-the-ruling" target="_blank">more about the ruling</a>). 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üáÆüá∑ Iran- Not happening.</strong> 
            Iran is preparing to reject a US nuclear proposal, calling it a ‚Äúnon-starter‚Äù that fails to meet its key demands: continued uranium enrichment and complete, upfront sanctions relief. Iranian officials argue that the proposal is one-sided and lacks trust-building guarantees (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-4-jun-25-worldwide-12-no-agreement" target="_blank">no agreement</a>). 
          </p>
         
